==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Residentiary
<hw>Res`i*den"tia*ry</hw> <pr>(-d?n"sh?-r?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[LL. <ets>residentiaris</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having residence;
<as>as, a canon <ex>residentary</ex>; a <ex>residentiary</ex>
guardian.</as></def> <rj><au>Dr. H. More.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Residentiary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Residentiary
<hw>Res`i*den"tia*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who is
resident.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>residentiary</qex>, or the frequent visitor of the
favored spot, . . . will discover that both have been there.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An ecclesiastic who keeps a certain
residence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Inhabitant; inhabiter; dweller;
sojourner.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Residentiaryship</ent>⟦br⟧
